HEADWORD: Left-handiness
<hw>Left"-hand`i*ness</hw>
<pr>(-⟦icr⟧*n⟦ecr⟧s)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state or
quality of being left-handed; awkwardness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An awkward address, ungraceful attitudes and actions, and a
certain <qex>left-handiness</qex> (if I may use the expression) proclaim
low education.</q> <rj><qau>Chesterfield.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>left-hander</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>lefthander</ent>⟦br⟧
